<br>
Anybody can equip the hammer, but it will only proc if you are level 50 or higher. The fact that the teleport is a weapon proc has led to some fun situations. Duel a party member or whack on a greenie until you are suddenly spirited away. Then just gate back when you've done your business in town.<br>
<br>
This quest requires that you have amiable or better VenrilSathir faction. This faction can be raised by handing four Sarnak war braids at a time to Captain Rottgrime. Sarnak war braids are easily obtained by killing Sarnak berserkers in Overthere.<br>
<br>
As most necros already know, your faction in OT can also be raised one level by being in skeletal form. (e.g. if you are normally indifferent, being a skeleton will raise you to amiable.) I raised my faction to indifferent by doing Rottgrimes quest, then I duelled a necro and had her cast Ignite Bones on me, which turned me into a skeleton long enough so I could get my hammer.<br>
<br>
For those who don't care to follow the link above, the quest is simple: hand a jade to the undead foreman and he gives you the hammer. Jade can be bought off the component vendor in the outpost.<br>
<br>
I have found the ability to teleport to Kunark at will immensely valuable. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 51st Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvalherji.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valherji</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/01 6:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Worker's Sledgemallet</span><hr size=1> If you plan on using this item, dont plan on ever fighting in Karnors, Kaesora, and probably a few other zones, as the mobs there have -VS faction. Once I found that out, I gave up on getting this item.<br>
